Hello learners!! 👋👋

Google Season of Docs is here! 🤩

Season of Docs supports documentation in open source by:

✅Providing funds to open source organizations to use for documentation projects.

✅Providing guides and support for open source organizations to help them understand their documentation needs.

✅Collecting data from open source organizations to better understand documentation practices.

✅Publishing case studies from open source organizations to share best practices.


📌 How does it work?

Season of Docs 2021 will operate as a grant program. Accepted organizations will receive between US$5,000 and US$15,000 to use for a documentation project.

📌 Participants and roles:

🔸 Organization administrators are members of the participating open source organizations who act as the principal Season of Docs contact for their organization.

🔸 Technical writers are not direct participants in the 2021 Season of Docs.

🔸 Google program administrators are program managers within Google who run the Season of Docs program.

⏰🛑 April 16 - November 16, 2021:
Hired technical writers work on documentation projects with guidance from organizations.

⏰🛑 May 17, 2021 at 18:00 UTC
Technical writer hiring deadline.

For further information please visit 👇

https://developers.google.com/season-of-docs/docs

Register at: 👇

https://developers.google.com/season-of-docs/docs


